results.name: Square array read by antidiagonals upwards: T(n,k) = n-th number with k odd divisors.
comment: T(n,k) is the n-th positive integer with exactly k odd divisors.
This is a permutation of the natural numbers.
T(n,k) is also the n-th number j with the property that the symmetric representation of sigma(j) has k subparts (cf. A279387). - _Omar E. Pol_, Dec 27 2016
T(n,k) is also the n-th positive integer with exactly k partitions into consecutive parts. - _Omar E. Pol_, Aug 16 2018
